tion" href="https://spore.social/@yoginho" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;yoginho&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111847279978259475</guid><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jan 2024 22:34:11 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>PsychoPy</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@psychopy/111850214229565648</link><description>Thanks for coming to our Pavlovia Surveys Features Showcase last week! In response to one of the questions from our attendees, check out this simple demo on how to use the Shelf to check for existing participant IDsüîç &lt;a href="https://www.psychopy.org/online/shelf.html#checking-existing-participant-ids" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;psychopy.org/online/shelf.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;#checking-existing-participant-ids&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111850214229565648</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 11:00:25 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carl Zimmer</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@Carl_Zimmer/111850543778506546</link><description>I‚Äôm on the Daily podcast today. I talked to Sabrina Tavernise about how DNA from Bronze Age skeletons is helping decipher modern diseases. &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/31/podcasts/the-daily/dna-illness.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nytimes.com/2024/01/31/podcast&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;s/the-daily/dna-illness.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111850543778506546</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 12:24:14 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111851708478345671</link><description>Voting in UK elections as a resident abroad...As fellow UK expatriates may know, the 15-year voting limit has been removed and it is theoretically possible for all UK citizens to vote.But it turns out not to be so simple. The documents that must be provided are not easy to arrange a few decades later.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111851708478345671</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 17:20:25 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111851721306099343</link><description>You are supposed to provide documentation for the last place you were registered to vote.It turns out I no longer have proof of residence there, that the council don't have archives of the electoral rolls and I don't think any potential attestor could truthfully affirm that I was registered to vote.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111851721306099343</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 17:23:41 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Glyn Moody</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@glynmoody/111846190330085059</link><description>Ministers plan to push cash-strapped English councils to sell assets - &lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2024/jan/30/ministers-plan-to-push-english-councils-to-sell-assets-to-plug-budget-holes-condemned" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;theguardian.com/uk-news/2024/j&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;an/30/ministers-plan-to-push-english-councils-to-sell-assets-to-plug-budget-holes-condemned&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; of course - this was the plan all along, asset stripping for their rich mates to buy at firesale prices...</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111851740652886007</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 17:28:36 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Blake Richards</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@tyrell_turing/111852463980486949</link><description>Our &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/OpenScope" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;OpenScope&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; collaboration with the Allen Institute is now up in J Neurosci!tl;dr - the responses to violations of a pattern in sequences of images evolve differently in apical dendrites versus somata of V1 pyramidal neurons:&lt;a href="https://www.jneurosci.org/content/44/5/e1009232023" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;jneurosci.org/content/44/5/e10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;09232023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;PS - Both the paper and the data are fully open!</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111852464052702728</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 20:32:33 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111852576193244516</link><description>How bad are citations as a metric? The world is already upside down. Clarivate can no longer produce a list of highly cited mathematicians. Obscure Chinese medical schools (without a maths department) are more cited than Princeton.&lt;a href="https://www.science.org/content/article/citation-cartels-help-some-mathematicians-and-their-universities-climb-rankings" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;science.org/content/article/ci&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;tation-cartels-help-some-mathematicians-and-their-universities-climb-rankings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;"Highly cited researcher" is on the cusp of becoming an insult in every field.We should really drive a stake through the heart of bibliometry once and for all.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111852576193244516</guid><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 21:01:06 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>CatSaladüêàü•ó (D.Burch) :blobcatrainbow:</title><link>https://infosec.exchange/@catsalad/111426154930652642</link><description>Google announced that starting in June 2024, ad blockers such as uBlock Origin &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/uBO" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;uBO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;will be disabled&lt;/strong&gt; in Chrome 127 and later with the rollout of Manifest V3 (&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/Mv3" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Mv3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).The new &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/Chrome" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Chrome&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; manifest will &lt;em&gt;prevent using custom filters&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;stops on demand updates&lt;/em&gt; of blocklist. Only &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/Google" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Google&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; authorized updates to browser extension will be allowed in the future, which mean an automatic win for Google in their battle to stop YouTube &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/AdBlockers" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;AdBlockers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/ManifestV3" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;ManifestV3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is deceitful and threatening to your privacy, and now is a good time to switch to &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/Firefox" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Firefox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mozilla.social/@mozilla" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;mozilla&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) and/or &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/TorBrowser" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;TorBrowser&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@torproject" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;torproject&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) if you haven't done so already!&lt;strong&gt;EFF (&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@eff" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;eff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) on Google‚Äôs Manifest V3&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;blockquote&gt;‚ö†Ô∏è‚Å†&lt;a href="https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2021/12/chrome-users-beware-manifest-v3-deceitful-and-threatening" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;eff.org/deeplinks/2021/12/chro&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;me-users-beware-manifest-v3-deceitful-and-threatening&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;‚ö†Ô∏è‚Å†&lt;a href="https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2021/12/googles-manifest-v3-still-hurts-privacy-security-innovation" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;eff.org/deeplinks/2021/12/goog&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;les-manifest-v3-still-hurts-privacy-security-innovation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chrome Manifest V3 Transition Timeline&lt;/strong&gt; (2023-11-16)&lt;blockquote&gt;üö©‚Å†&lt;a href="https://developer.chrome.com/blog/resuming-the-transition-to-mv3/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;developer.chrome.com/blog/resu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class